{
  "texts": [
    "As a result, the depth of the encoderdecoder architecture may differ from application to application.",
    "Although high success is achieved, especially in very deep networks, the logarithmic increase in the number of processes can be a significant disadvantage [10].",
    "In addition, it is a method that requires a large number of parameters.",
    "This situation causes a very long time and process costs, especially in training the model.",
    "• In some cases, important features can be lost due to step connections used in encoder-decoder blocks."
  ]
}